narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I learned a lot about the Italian language and culture. I was exposed to vocabulary, grammar, and conversation skills.
This class allowed me to further my learning of a new language.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: The strengths were structured exposure to the language. Also, we had snacks sometimes. The weaknesses were that the level of class engagement sometimes declined, making the class experience boring.
This course is very engaging and the professors are incredible.
Pacing was very good. I enjoyed this class and how it was taught.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes, I would absolutely recommend this course to another student - specifically because I really enjoyed my instructor.
Yes. Italian is a beautiful language and the department for Italian at Yale is excellent.
